00:00:28.940 --> 00:00:29.530
For example,

00:00:29.530 --> 00:00:31.110
if I'm going to Germany,

00:00:31.110 --> 00:00:32.720
I will decide,

00:00:32.720 --> 00:00:32.880
say,

00:00:32.880 --> 00:00:36.300
a month ahead of time that I will start easing myself into German.

00:00:36.300 --> 00:00:37.120
So what does this mean?

00:00:37.120 --> 00:00:41.910
This means that I'll start off light and this usually entails finding some music in German

00:00:41.910 --> 00:00:41.910
,

00:00:41.910 --> 00:00:46.340
maybe listening to a little bit of German radio online and stuff like that for a few days

00:00:46.340 --> 00:00:47.060
during that time.

00:00:47.060 --> 00:00:52.160
Also search for some podcasts and I'll start using those and slowly but surely I'll start

00:00:52.160 --> 00:00:57.850
easing into maybe reading a couple articles online and maybe finding some online courses or

00:00:57.850 --> 00:01:00.660
something like that so I can ease myself back into German.

00:01:00.660 --> 00:01:03.620
So hopefully by the time I get there,

00:01:03.620 --> 00:01:06.960
my German level is pretty much where I left off.

00:01:06.960 --> 00:01:08.140
Last time I studied it.

00:01:08.140 --> 00:01:12.020
